A 13-year-old girl was allegedly abducted at gunpoint &amp; raped by 10 men in Nyanga. CAPE TOWN - Seven men accused of the rape of a 13-year-old girl in Nyanga will spend the next week behind bars.The suspects, between the ages of 18 and 20, were arrested shortly after the attack last weekend and made their first appearance in the Wynberg Magistrates Court on Friday.It's alleged the victim was abducted at gunpoint by one of the accused while walking along Robert Sibukwe Road last week.One of the seven young men, accused of the rape of the 13-year-old girl, pulled his jersey over his face and sobbed bitterly as he entered the dock.All seven accused have opted to appoint their own lawyers for their next court appearance on Friday.The court heard the girl was raped by 10 men and three suspects are still being sought.Western Cape Social Development is assisting the victim and her family. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)